Originally ripped by Terminal Escape, posted on July 05, 2013 Description from Terminal Escape:
Simply put, this is probably the best international hardcore/punk mix tape I have ever heard. Perfect selection of unknown bangers and under the radar classics interspersed with a few tracks that should be familiar with punks who have taken the time to dig a little. I dare say that a tape like this might not have been able to exist (but for an elite few) in the pre-internet years, but the ensuing conversation would detract from the sheer power of the contents of today's link. Do it. SOLO SE OYE PUNK vol. 4
